@member-directory-search
Feature: Member Directory Search
  As a signed-in member
  I want to search the member directory by name or skill
  So that I can find other members to work with

  Background:
    Given a member directory with several registered members
    And a signed-in member

  # Why: Core search path — the minimal complete definition of the feature.
  @task:TASK-MDS-002
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Searching by name returns matching members
    Given a member named "Priya" is in the directory
    When the member searches the directory for "Priya"
    Then the results should include Priya

  # Why: Skill search is the second entry point named in the ask.
  @task:TASK-MDS-002
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Searching by skill returns members with that skill
    Given a member in the directory lists throwing as a skill
    When the member searches the directory for the skill "throwing"
    Then the results should include that member

  # Why: A result must lead somewhere useful — the profile summary is the payoff.
  @task:TASK-MDS-004
  @key-example
  Scenario: Opening a search result shows the member's profile summary
    Given a search that returned at least one member
    When the member opens one of the results
    Then that member's profile summary should be shown

  # Why: Just-inside boundary of the assumed page size keeps long result sets usable.
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=low] A results page holds at most twenty members
  @task:TASK-MDS-002
  @boundary
  Scenario: Results beyond the page size appear on the next page
    Given more members match the search than fit on one results page
    When the member searches the directory
    Then the first page should hold the page limit of members
    And the remaining matches should be available on the next page

  # Why: Just-outside boundary of the assumed minimum query length — should be refused.
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=low] A search query must be at least two characters long
  @task:TASK-MDS-002
  @boundary @negative
  Scenario: A query shorter than the minimum length is refused
    Given the member is on the directory search
    When the member searches for a single character
    Then the search should be refused
    And the member should be told the query is too short

  # Why: The directory is for members — visitors must not browse it.
  @task:TASK-MDS-003
  @negative
  Scenario: A visitor who is not signed in cannot search the directory
    Given a visitor who is not signed in
    When the visitor tries to search the directory
    Then the search should be refused

  # Why: An empty query is the most common invalid input.
  @task:TASK-MDS-002
  @negative
  Scenario: Searching with an empty query is refused
    Given the member is on the directory search
    When the member searches with an empty query
    Then the search should be refused

  # Why: Namesakes must not shadow each other in results.
  @task:TASK-MDS-004
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Two members sharing the same name are both listed
    Given two different members share the same name
    When the member searches the directory for that name
    Then both members should appear in the results

  # Why: Members control their own visibility — an opted-out member must never leak.
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=low] Members can opt out of appearing in the directory
  @task:TASK-MDS-002
  @edge-case
  Scenario: A member who has opted out never appears in results
    Given a member who has opted out of the directory
    When another member searches for that member's name
    Then the results should not include the opted-out member
